			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Some Christmas songs are a bit spooky. I&#8217;m thinking especially of &#8220;Santa Claus Is Comin&#8217; To Town&#8221;, which makes that merry old elf out to be almost Orwellian. Since I like to write alternate lyrics to songs, I made the following adaptation of &#8220;Santa Claus Is Comin&#8217; To Town&#8221;&#8230;</p>
<p>You&#8217;d better watch out, you&#8217;d better not cry<br />
You&#8217;d better not pout, I&#8217;m telling you why<br />
Santa Claus is comin&#8217; to town!</p>
<p>He&#8217;s making a list, he&#8217;s checking it twice<br />
His database says who&#8217;s naughty or nice<br />
Santa Claus is comin&#8217; to town!</p>
<p>He spies on you in the night-time<br />
He spies on you in the day<br />
He keeps track of all your movements<br />
He works for the CIA</p>
<p>You&#8217;d better watch out, you&#8217;d better not cry<br />
You&#8217;d better not pout, I&#8217;m telling you why<br />
Santa Claus is comin&#8217; to town!</p>
<p>The kids in Girl and Boy Land<br />
They never will be free<br />
They&#8217;re in the Santa Youth League<br />
They&#8217;ll conform like you and me</p>
<p>You&#8217;d better watch out, you&#8217;d better not cry<br />
You&#8217;d better not pout, I&#8217;m telling you why<br />
Santa Claus is comin&#8217; to town!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
