			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Even people who love music probably prefer certain periods, instruments, genres, and the like. I try to have big ears, but I must say that I&#8217;m not particularly fond of the flute or most woodwinds (except perhaps the oboe). And I really don&#8217;t like the triangle. For instance recently I was listening to Z &#269;esk&#253;ch luh&#367; a h&#225;j&#367; (&#8221;From Bohemia&#8217;s Woods and Fields&#8221;) by Bed&#345;ich Smetana and the incessant sounding of the triangle nearly spoiled it for me. The same goes for some of the symphonic poems of Anton&#237;n Dvo&#345;&#225;k.</p>
<p>Just my musical pet peeve of the day&#8230;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
