			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As America slides ever closer to political <a href='http://ismbook.com/absolutism.html'>absolutism</a>, I find myself ever more attracted to musical absolutism. For many years now some of my favorite pieces of music have been Bach&#8217;s more absolute works, such as the Art of the Fugue, the Keyboard Partitas, and the Cello Suites. Lately also I&#8217;ve been listening a lot to the 24 preludes and fugues by Dmitri Shostakovich (as recorded by Keith Jarrett). I&#8217;ve also just discovered the music of German bassist-composer Eberhard Weber, which I look forward to exploring more fully in the coming months. To me, there is something deeply calming about such absolute music &#8212; no lyrics, no program, no flash, no bombast, just pure, unadorned musical thinking.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
